<TITLE> Fog disrupts communications </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 15 (bdnews24.com) Ferry services on Paturia-Doulatdia and Mawa-Kaorakandi routes remained suspended for several hours, disrupting communications between Dhaka and southern districts. bdnews24.com Manikganj correspondent reported that poor visibility caused by thick fog halted ferry operations on Paturia-Doulatdia route from 3am to 5am. Ferries resumed operation after 5am, Ashraf Ullah, manager (commerce) of Bangladesh Inland Water Transport Corporation said. He said as fog intensified after 1am eight ferries remained stranded in Doulatdia pier. Over 300 goods trucks and 100 passenger buses were stranded on both the piers. Madaripur correspondent said ferries could not operate from 3:30am to 8:30am because of heavy fog on the Mawa-Kaorakandi route. bdnews
